<item>
            <title>[HBASE-13511] Derive data keys with HKDF</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-13511</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When we are locally managing master key material, when users have supplied their own data key material, derive the actual data keys using HKDF (&lt;a href=&quot;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5869&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc5869&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;DK&apos; = HKDF(S, DK, MK)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;S = salt&lt;br/&gt;
DK = user supplied data key&lt;br/&gt;
MK = master key&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;DK&apos; = derived data key for the HFile&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;User supplied key material may be weak or an attacker may have some partial knowledge of it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Where we generate random data keys we can still use HKDF as a way to mix more entropy into the secure random generator. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;DK&apos; = HKDF(R, MK)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;where&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;R = random key material drawn from the system&apos;s secure random generator&lt;br/&gt;
MK = master key&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(Salting isn&apos;t useful here because salt S and R would be drawn from the same pool, so will not have statistical independence.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
