                            <comment id="14503260" author="apurtell" created="Mon, 20 Apr 2015 17:31:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We can just drop this in place with full backwards compatibility. Encrypted data keys are stored with the HFiles and used directly after unwrapping. Changing data keys doesn&apos;t affect old files, it only applies to new writes.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Recall that data keys are encrypted with the master key and stored in the file trailer, and the rest of the file is encrypted with the data key. We can have a good master key protecting data keys, but weak (user supplied) data keys leaving HFile data vulnerable to cryptanalysis. We shouldn&apos;t trust user supplied data keys to be good.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
